  "prompt": "In Japanese, what is the meaning of \"Kimigayo\"?",
  "response": "\"Kimigayo\" (\u541b\u304c\u4ee3) is the title of the national anthem of Japan. The meaning of \"Kimigayo\" can be translated as \"His Imperial Majesty's Reign\" or \"The Emperor's Reign.\" The lyrics express a wish for the emperor's reign to continue for thousands of years. The phrase \"Kimigayo\" itself is often interpreted as a wish for enduring peace and prosperity in Japan.",
